        NAV> r

I wanted SEDIT r, but got ALDO r.  In autolisp since we don't have
explicitely multiple-values (and no-value), all functions should
return something. So we should make an expression argument mandatory
to the aldo r command.  In that case, when it's not given on the r
command line, the command processing should ask the user for a return
value.

